originalText.text: Don’t come here unless you want your vehicle damaged! I brought my car here cause I couldn’t find parking in the neighborhood. When I came back to pick it up at the lot just a few hrs later the car was parked near their office with my windows rolled down which took my attention away from noticing any differences at the moment. When I got home and parked under the sun I noticed that the edge of my driver door from the door handle down had scuffs and chips of white paint along the edge of the door, which seemed to have been white paint from the garage walls at Mutual 82nd Parking. I spoke to the manager and he quickly denied any damages, explaining he personally handled my vehicle and doesn’t recall opening my driver door into any walls, he also mentioned that I can put a claim in but it’ll get denied. I never parked near a white wall or any walls for that matter so how else would this happen. I paid $12 to have my car door damaged. Park here at your own risk.
